In LaTeX, you can create a sentence with the words "feel, must, he, something" in that specific order by simply writing the sentence within the `document` environment. Here is an example of how you might structure it:

```latex
\documentclass{article}

\begin{document}

He must feel something.

\end{document}
```

This will produce a document with the sentence "He must feel something." Make sure to compile the LaTeX document with a LaTeX editor or command-line tool to see the output.
